data.enText: the bone structure that forms the head and surrounds and protects the brain
Her skull was crammed with too many thoughts.

data.chText: 那笨头笨脑的家伙什么时候才能明白我再也不想见他了！
data.enText: When will he get it into his thick skull that I never want to see him again!

tr: the bony skeleton of the head of vertebrates

value.def: Your skull is the bony part of your head which encloses your brain.

example.ex: Her husband was later treated for a fractured skull.
example.tran: 她丈夫后来接受了颅骨骨折治疗。

trans: 骷髅旗，骷髅画(旧时画在海盗旗上，现在作为警示印在危险物品的容器上)
